Notebook[{
Cell["InfraPoint", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"b3cce8e5-df0f-453f-a4fd-4b34a92e5cbf"],

Cell["[LLM Generated]", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"8f0e761a-a198-4bb5-9215-e8e158b52119"],

Cell["\<\
InfraPoint is the wrapper head for vertex realisations of the point \
primitive. InfraPoint[v] is the unary form; InfraPoint[{v1, \[Ellipsis], vk}] \
is the multi-realisation form. Every Find* finder that returns points \
(FindInfraPoint, FindInfraMidpoint, FindInfraReflection, CompleteInfraEquilateralTriangle, \
FindInfraCommonPoint, FindInfraPerpendicular, and the 5-vertex ExtendInfraSegment form) \
emits a List of unary InfraPoint[{v}] wrappers. Wrapping that List with \
InfraPoint @ \[Ellipsis] collapses it to the multi form via auto-flatten.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c29ba5ce-5a47-4aaf-abb9-7db6b025745d"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"18dba56e-da54-4d13-9e6e-cf8e42159b2d"],

